    {
      "id": "about",
      "type": "page",
      "label": "About",
      "children": [
        {
          "id": "about_general_text",
          "type": "text",
          "text": "TAI - Assess Bias\n===============================\n\nThis custom step allows the user to evaluate predictive model bias across sensitive groups using the SAS procedure PROC ASSESSBIAS. The step takes a scored input table (containing a predicted probability column, (P_[ColumnName]) produced by a previous statistical/modeling step) and produces a series of tables that help the user understand fairness in their model:\n\nGroup Metrics — including number of observations, average squared error, and absolute error per sensitive group.\nMax Difference Between Sensitive Groups — depicting the \"worst case\" disparity across groups.\nBias Metrics — derived from the group metrics, capturing differences in average prediction, misclassification rate, and related measures.\n\nThe closer a bias metric value is to 0, the more similar the treatment was across sensitive groups.\n\nMore information about PROC ASSESSBIAS: https://go.documentation.sas.com/doc/en/pgmsascdc/default/casactml/casactml_assessbias_toc.htm",
          "visible": ""
        },
        {
          "id": "prerequisites_section",
          "type": "section",
          "label": "Pre-requisites",
          "open": true,
          "visible": "",
          "children": [
            {
              "id": "prerequisites_text",
              "type": "text",
              "text": "• Access to a scored input table that contains a predicted probability column (typically P_[TargetEvent]) produced by an upstream modeling step (e.g., PROC LOGISTIC, PROC HPFOREST, PROC GENMOD).\n• A SAS Viya environment with PROC ASSESSBIAS available (sasviya/casactml action set).\n• The input table must include the target variable and at least one sensitive variable to assess.",
              "visible": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "documentation_section",
          "type": "section",
          "label": "Documentation",
          "open": true,
          "visible": "",
          "children": [
            {
              "id": "documentation_text",
              "type": "text",
              "text": "PROC ASSESSBIAS reference:\nhttps://go.documentation.sas.com/doc/en/pgmsascdc/default/casactml/casactml_assessbias_toc.htm\n\nSAS Studio Custom Steps UI Guidelines:\nhttps://github.com/sassoftware/sas-studio-custom-steps/blob/main/docs/UI-guidelines.md",
              "visible": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "configuration_section",
          "type": "section",
          "label": "Configuration Tab",
          "open": true,
          "visible": "",
          "children": [
            {
              "id": "configuration_text",
              "type": "text",
              "text": "1. Input table — Select the scored table that contains the predicted probability column, the target variable, and the sensitive variable.\n2. Predicted probability variable — Select one or more probability columns (typically P_[TargetEvent]) generated by an upstream modeling step.\n3. Sensitive variable — Select exactly one column representing the sensitive grouping (e.g., a PII or demographic variable) on which bias will be assessed.\n4. Target variable — Select the actual target/outcome column.\n5. Target level — Choose Interval or Nominal.\n6. Target event (visible when Target level = Nominal) — Select the event level of interest from the target variable.\n7. P variables — Optional column used in the fitstat statement.\n8. P event — Optional event for the FitStat probability variable, referenced from the target variable.\n9. Delimiter (visible when P event is set) — Choose the delimiter used by the FitStat statement: space, semicolon, asterisk, period, or comma.",
              "visible": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "options_section",
          "type": "section",
          "label": "Options tab",
          "open": true,
          "visible": "",
          "children": [
            {
              "id": "options_text",
              "type": "text",
              "text": "1. Cutoff ratio — Classification cutoff for predicted probabilities (range 0–1, default 0.5).\n2. Number of bins — Number of bins used for binned bias metrics (min 2, default 20).\n3. Number of cuts — Number of cutpoints used for cut-based bias metrics (range 2–100, default 100).\n4. Selection depth — Selection depth percentage for depth-based metrics (range 1–100, default 10).\n5. Frequency — Optional frequency column.\n6. Weight — Optional observation weight column.",
              "visible": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "usage_section",
          "type": "section",
          "label": "Usage",
          "open": true,
          "visible": "",
          "children": [
            {
              "id": "usage_text",
              "text": "Required inputs:\n\t 1. Input table\n\t 2. Predicted probability variable\n\t 3. Sensitive variable\n\t 4. Target variable\n\nIf any of these are missing, the step will not execute PROC ASSESSBIAS; instead, an error message saying \"PROC ASSESSBIAS will not run because one or more required variables are missing.\"",
              "type": "text",
              "visible": ""
            }
          ]
        },
